WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.958
Support Admin Watch on
kissasia.cam or kisskh.org

00:07.958 --> 00:09.916
[staticky ringing builds]

00:11.125 --> 00:13.125
You are my world.

00:14.333 --> 00:16.250
- [weapon fires]
- [Lucy] Where are you taking him?

00:17.625 --> 00:19.875
To the real world.
You should see it sometime.

00:19.875 --> 00:26.333
You can change the future
if you can bring me to Moldaver.

00:27.208 --> 00:28.958
- Just my head.
- Ow.

00:28.958 --> 00:31.500
[Wilzig] <i>This is the only way
to get your dad back.</i>

00:31.500 --> 00:34.041
- [screams]
- [Quintus] <i>Aspirant Dane?</i>

00:34.166 --> 00:35.375
You're aware of their injury?

00:36.291 --> 00:37.791
[Titus] <i>Shoot it!</i>

00:37.791 --> 00:41.125
You stupid motherfucker,
you know this is all your fault.

00:41.125 --> 00:42.458
They'll kill you for this.

00:42.458 --> 00:43.791
[Maximus] <i>They don't have to find out.</i>

00:43.791 --> 00:45.125
It's the Brotherhood.

00:45.125 --> 00:47.416
<i>- They'll find out.</i>
- [distant whirring]

00:47.416 --> 00:50.041
They want a head, we give them a head.

00:50.041 --> 00:51.291
You're supposed to come with me.

00:51.291 --> 00:53.500
They're never gonna stop looking.
Trust me.

00:54.833 --> 00:58.291
[Miss Williams] <i>America has been locked
in a resource war.</i>

00:58.291 --> 01:01.125
<i>Vault-Tec bought the means
to end that war.</i>

01:01.125 --> 01:03.875
<i>Cold fusion. Infinite energy.</i>

01:03.875 --> 01:05.458
- [Snake Oil Salesman] Is-is that a...
- [Thaddeus] Fusion core?

01:05.458 --> 01:08.250
You don't see those around much
anymore, do you?

01:08.375 --> 01:12.333
What is the ultimate weapon
to destroy your competition?

01:12.333 --> 01:14.208
<i>It's time.</i>

01:14.208 --> 01:16.250
[Cooper] <i>You ever think
about working somewhere else?</i>

01:16.250 --> 01:18.166
Vault-Tec exists with or without me.

01:18.166 --> 01:20.625
It doesn't do anyone any good to complain
from the sidelines.

01:20.625 --> 01:24.000
- It's a listening device.
- You want me to spy on my wife?

01:25.291 --> 01:27.166
[Norm] <i>When my mother died,
what happened to her Pip-Boy?</i>

01:27.166 --> 01:28.500
It was buried with her.

01:28.500 --> 01:30.458
<i>I buried her myself.</i>

01:30.458 --> 01:33.666
<i>Me... and your father.</i>

01:33.666 --> 01:35.291
[dramatic music playing]

01:35.291 --> 01:37.916
[clanking and hissing]

01:39.250 --> 01:40.250
[Norm] <i>Hello?</i>

01:41.250 --> 01:42.250
[static crackling]

01:52.250 --> 01:55.208
[Vertibird approaching]

02:13.291 --> 02:16.000
[dramatic music playing]

02:20.791 --> 02:21.833
Find me.

02:22.916 --> 02:24.250
I will.

02:28.416 --> 02:30.625
[indistinct radio chatter]

02:45.041 --> 02:46.708
[officer over radio] <i>Filly clear
for landing.</i>

02:46.708 --> 02:49.791
<i>The locals put up a fight, but so did we.</i>
[laughs]

02:57.541 --> 02:59.541
♪ ♪

03:04.458 --> 03:06.458
♪ ♪

03:26.083 --> 03:28.083
♪ ♪

03:56.541 --> 03:58.916
You're wearing the Knight's red.

04:00.541 --> 04:02.833
Where's your Knight?

04:05.875 --> 04:07.625
He's dead.

04:12.125 --> 04:16.250
This is not the first time
a Brother in your company

04:16.250 --> 04:18.875
has fallen into misfortune...

04:21.833 --> 04:23.375
...is it?

04:33.083 --> 04:36.333
- [device whirring]
- I fear you lied then.

04:37.458 --> 04:39.875
[cleric] No artifact, m'lord.

04:39.875 --> 04:42.791
Just as you lie now.

04:44.833 --> 04:46.666
Wait, wait, wait!

04:46.666 --> 04:49.875
- [groans] Wait, wait, wait.
- [chanting last rites]

04:49.875 --> 04:51.583
[Maximus] Please, listen to me!

04:51.583 --> 04:54.500
I can get you the real head.

04:54.500 --> 04:56.083
[Quintus] Confess.

04:56.083 --> 04:58.458
[Maximus] Don't kill me
and I can lead you to it!

04:59.458 --> 05:01.500
[panting]

05:01.500 --> 05:04.750
[Maximus groaning]

05:04.750 --> 05:07.250
[groans] I can help you!

05:07.250 --> 05:09.458
Please, m'lord.

05:10.583 --> 05:12.958
My injury was my own doing. Not his.

05:14.500 --> 05:17.625
Please...
Please, I know where the head is!

05:17.625 --> 05:19.916
For the sake of the Brotherhood,
please listen to him!

05:19.916 --> 05:22.666
[Maximus panting]

05:22.666 --> 05:25.208
Such a display of loyalty.

05:25.208 --> 05:28.666
Don't see that much anymore.

05:43.500 --> 05:46.500
[somber music playing]

05:58.208 --> 06:02.250
[Quintus] You think you're the first
squire who coveted his Knight's armor?

06:05.583 --> 06:07.875
How did Titus die?

06:07.875 --> 06:10.291
He died running.

06:10.291 --> 06:11.750
[sighs softly]

06:12.750 --> 06:15.750
The Brotherhood has lost its way.

06:17.625 --> 06:20.916
We once ruled the Wasteland...

06:23.916 --> 06:28.333
And yet power is taken, not given.

06:28.333 --> 06:31.208
A lesson you seem to have learned.

06:39.500 --> 06:43.208
So, if what you say is true,

06:43.208 --> 06:46.541
and you can lead us to the relic,

06:46.541 --> 06:50.166
then together, you and I,

06:50.166 --> 06:52.916
we will take power.

06:54.708 --> 06:57.333
And with it...

06:57.333 --> 07:00.250
we will start a new Brotherhood.

07:00.250 --> 07:06.708
With me as its head,
and the likes of you as its sword.

07:14.750 --> 07:18.708
Your entire life,
you've been looking for a home.

07:18.708 --> 07:21.625
[dramatic music playing]

07:24.625 --> 07:27.208
♪ ♪

07:28.541 --> 07:31.166
Build one with me.

07:39.208 --> 07:41.208
♪ ♪

07:46.125 --> 07:47.750
[weapon cocks]

08:06.833 --> 08:09.250
[suspenseful music playing]

08:26.791 --> 08:28.791
[giggling]

08:33.791 --> 08:35.041
It's her.

08:50.458 --> 08:52.458
♪ ♪

08:57.000 --> 08:59.458
[barking]

08:59.458 --> 09:02.541
[intriguing music playing]

09:12.583 --> 09:14.000
[wind gusting]

09:15.833 --> 09:18.833
[gentle music playing]

09:24.833 --> 09:26.750
[Barb] Well, thank you for the ride.

09:26.750 --> 09:29.875
[Cooper] Well, it's the least I could do
after I bungled your oil change.

09:29.875 --> 09:32.375
[chuckles] Well, I appreciate you trying.

09:32.375 --> 09:34.958
You know, most guys with a ride this nice,

09:34.958 --> 09:37.833
they wouldn't be willing
to get their hands dirty.

09:41.041 --> 09:43.250
Okay.

09:43.250 --> 09:45.375
- I love you.
- Love you, too.

09:47.250 --> 09:49.125
- Have a great day.
- Thank you, Coop.

09:49.125 --> 09:50.625
Okay.

09:55.708 --> 09:57.541
[grunts softly]

09:57.541 --> 09:59.958
[festive music playing over radio]

09:59.958 --> 10:01.458
Coop!

10:01.458 --> 10:03.500
- [chuckling]
- Ah.

10:03.500 --> 10:06.208
- Good to see you, buddy.
- Yeah.

10:07.458 --> 10:10.416
- What's wrong?
- Uh, my Pip-Boy.

10:10.416 --> 10:14.583
It's been acting strange.
The transmitter is always activated...

10:14.583 --> 10:17.125
[Bud] Well, maybe take it over to the boys
in IT, have them take a look...

10:17.125 --> 10:19.125
[Barb] No, no, I can fix it myself.

10:19.125 --> 10:21.625
I just need to figure out where
the Pip-Boy is trying to transmit to...

10:21.625 --> 10:24.291
I-I'm heading out. I promised Janey
that I would teach her some roping.

10:24.291 --> 10:26.958
Oh, yeah? I don't have kids myself.

10:26.958 --> 10:29.000
But I do have a training program
for up-and-coming executives,

10:29.000 --> 10:30.500
and that's basically
the same thing. [laughs]

10:30.500 --> 10:32.791
I imagine Barb told you about it?

10:34.750 --> 10:37.375
- Uh... no. No.
- Oh.

10:37.375 --> 10:38.666
Well, I call it Bud's Buds.

10:38.666 --> 10:40.791
The basic idea is
that the biggest obstacle to achievement

10:40.791 --> 10:42.625
has been the brevity
of the human lifespan.

10:42.625 --> 10:45.541
It's prevented us from working
on projects that require centuries,

10:45.541 --> 10:47.083
maybe even millennia, to see through.

10:47.083 --> 10:50.000
So ideally, Bud's Buds will keep
my project on track

10:50.000 --> 10:52.500
- centuries into the future. Nifty, huh?
- Bud.

10:52.500 --> 10:54.000
- We're getting late.
- Oh, yes.

10:54.000 --> 10:55.583
- Let's go.
- Big day today.

10:55.583 --> 10:57.625
- [taps on car]
- Yeah.

10:57.625 --> 10:58.958
Good luck.

11:01.250 --> 11:03.250
[sighs]

11:03.250 --> 11:07.333
[Bud] <i>Hey, maybe, uh, maybe we could
all go to Café Cabana sometime?</i>

11:07.333 --> 11:08.750
<i>You, me and Coop?</i>

11:08.750 --> 11:10.208
<i>Oh! Sorry.</i>

11:10.208 --> 11:12.500
[Barb] <i>Has your Pip-Boy
been acting strangely?</i>

11:12.500 --> 11:14.500
[Bud] <i>No. Why?
What's wrong with yours?</i>

11:14.500 --> 11:16.291
[Barb] <i>I'm not sure yet.</i>

11:16.291 --> 11:17.791
- [loud static]
- [clicks tongue]

11:17.791 --> 11:19.125
Fuck.

11:20.375 --> 11:21.791
[sighs]

11:26.250 --> 11:28.166
[tense music playing]

11:28.166 --> 11:30.250
♪ ♪

11:45.333 --> 11:47.333
♪ ♪

12:01.875 --> 12:03.875
[wind blowing]

12:14.958 --> 12:16.166
Lucy.

12:17.166 --> 12:18.166
Dad.

12:18.166 --> 12:20.041
[sighs]

12:24.333 --> 12:26.208
[ghoul snarling softly]

12:26.208 --> 12:28.291
[breathing heavily]

12:30.458 --> 12:32.000
[Moldaver] Welcome.

12:36.875 --> 12:40.083
[ghoul snarling]

12:41.625 --> 12:43.875
[growling]

12:43.875 --> 12:45.375
[Moldaver] Join us.

12:45.375 --> 12:48.041
It's my turn to host, isn't it?

12:48.041 --> 12:50.291
[snarling]

12:54.291 --> 12:56.875
I've had a lot of time
to think about this moment.

12:59.708 --> 13:02.500
You wouldn't believe the things
that went through my head.

13:02.500 --> 13:04.000
[ghoul snarling]

13:06.708 --> 13:08.166
One night, I...

13:08.166 --> 13:12.208
actually tried to stuff an old grenade
into the neck hole.

13:15.208 --> 13:17.500
Guess I... [inhales deeply]

13:17.500 --> 13:20.333
was gonna walk in here and...

13:20.333 --> 13:22.041
blow everybody up.

13:23.125 --> 13:24.541
But it's...

13:24.541 --> 13:27.166
not really how I was raised.

13:30.541 --> 13:32.291
So...

13:32.291 --> 13:34.125
if you don't mind,

13:34.125 --> 13:36.208
I'm gonna keep things civil.

13:39.708 --> 13:41.125
[ghoul snarling]

13:41.125 --> 13:43.166
Brought you your friend.

13:43.166 --> 13:44.833
Just like he asked.

13:45.833 --> 13:46.958
[snarls]

13:46.958 --> 13:49.041
[tool whirring]

13:56.666 --> 13:59.083
Now, please...

14:00.083 --> 14:01.666
...give me my dad back.

14:01.666 --> 14:04.083
[ghoul snarls]

14:04.083 --> 14:05.958
Very well.

14:09.125 --> 14:11.041
[dramatic music playing]

14:11.041 --> 14:12.875
♪ ♪

14:12.875 --> 14:14.875
But, first...

14:17.208 --> 14:20.000
...what if I tell you
how I know your father?

14:21.000 --> 14:22.833
Who he really is?

14:24.875 --> 14:26.833
[Hank] No. Lucy,

14:26.833 --> 14:29.083
- don't listen to her.
- You think your father

14:29.083 --> 14:30.916
was born in a vault.

14:31.916 --> 14:33.666
Like you.

14:35.875 --> 14:38.208
<i>Like your brother.</i>

14:38.208 --> 14:39.958
- [male voice] <i>The key to the future of--</i>
- [clanking and whirring]

14:39.958 --> 14:42.458
<i>- No, no, I'll get it this time.</i>
- Hello?

14:42.458 --> 14:44.458
<i>The key to the future of humanity--</i>

14:44.458 --> 14:45.875
- [clanking]
<i>- Oh!</i>

14:45.875 --> 14:47.625
<i>The-the-the key to the future of human--</i>

14:47.625 --> 14:49.083
- [clanking]
- [laughing] <i>Oh, no.</i>

14:49.083 --> 14:50.583
<i>This is ridiculous.</i>

14:51.625 --> 14:52.958
<i>The key to the future of humanity--</i>

14:52.958 --> 14:55.583
- [clanking]
<i>- Nope. Try.</i>

14:55.583 --> 14:57.583
- [Norm] Hello?
<i>- Nope.</i>

14:57.583 --> 14:59.416
<i>The key to the future of humanity--</i>

14:59.416 --> 15:01.750
- [clanking]
<i>- Ugh, I'm gonna get it.</i>

15:01.750 --> 15:03.208
[chuckles] <i>I'll get it. Don't you worry.</i>

15:03.208 --> 15:06.166
[chuckles] <i>The key to--
the key to the future of humanity--</i>

15:06.166 --> 15:08.041
- [clanking]
<i>- Oh!</i> [chuckles]

15:08.041 --> 15:10.375
<i>Now this is just ridiculous.</i>

15:11.375 --> 15:12.500
<i>A great game of the--</i>

15:12.500 --> 15:14.333
[mutters] <i>Oh.</i>

15:14.333 --> 15:18.083
[laughs] <i>All right, all right,
this one's it. I'll get it this time.</i>

15:18.083 --> 15:20.958
<i>The key to the future of humanity is a--</i>

15:20.958 --> 15:23.708
<i>Uh, nope. Just maybe I have to--</i>

15:23.708 --> 15:25.250
<i>Oh. Ah.</i>

15:25.250 --> 15:27.208
<i>Thank you, Betty.</i>

15:28.291 --> 15:29.458
<i>Wait, you're not Betty.</i>

15:29.458 --> 15:31.083
<i>Or Hank.</i>

15:32.583 --> 15:36.291
<i>You share only 50% of Hank MacLean's DNA.</i>

15:37.375 --> 15:38.666
I'm...

15:38.666 --> 15:40.000
- his son.
<i>- No.</i>

15:40.000 --> 15:42.041
<i>No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no!</i>

15:42.041 --> 15:43.250
What are you?

15:43.250 --> 15:45.666
<i>Initiate Protocol 53.</i>

15:45.666 --> 15:47.125
[dramatic music playing]

15:51.750 --> 15:54.000
[sighs] <i>Now, sorry, just hold still.</i>

15:54.000 --> 15:55.500
- Who are you?
<i>- Wait.</i>

15:55.500 --> 15:57.791
<i>Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.
I won't answer your questions</i>

15:57.791 --> 15:59.750
<i>unless you let me inject you with this.</i>

16:01.291 --> 16:05.708
<i>All right, don't move.
The secret must be guarded.</i>

16:05.708 --> 16:07.208
<i>Don't-don't go in there.</i>

16:07.208 --> 16:08.708
<i>Don't you go in there!</i>

16:08.708 --> 16:11.000
<i>Don't read anything in there!
Or turn on the lights.</i>

16:11.000 --> 16:15.333
<i>Don't you access the info tree
or look at the terminal.</i>

16:15.333 --> 16:16.833
<i>Wait! Just...</i>

16:16.833 --> 16:19.583
<i>stay right there. Stop.</i>

16:19.583 --> 16:21.666
<i>I'm coming!</i>

16:21.666 --> 16:23.500
What is this place?

16:25.333 --> 16:27.625
[Cooper] Any idea when Barb will be back?

16:27.625 --> 16:29.125
I'm sorry. She's in a meeting.

16:29.125 --> 16:31.500
Something about vertical integration or--

16:31.500 --> 16:32.791
Above my pay grade.

16:32.791 --> 16:35.125
- Mine, too. [chuckles]
- Ha.

16:36.541 --> 16:38.333
By the way, Mr. Howard,

16:38.333 --> 16:40.666
there's a new guy who works with Barb.

16:40.666 --> 16:42.208
Henry.

16:42.208 --> 16:44.375
He's a really big fan of yours.

16:44.375 --> 16:46.541
Yes. Henry.

16:46.541 --> 16:48.958
He has called the house a few times.

16:48.958 --> 16:50.416
Do you mind if I bring him by?

16:50.416 --> 16:52.458
Just to meet you for a moment?

16:52.458 --> 16:53.791
Of course.

16:53.791 --> 16:55.250
Yeah. Always happy to meet a fan.

16:58.833 --> 17:00.375
[sighs]

17:00.375 --> 17:01.791
[door opens]

17:03.000 --> 17:04.958
- [door closes]
- [exhales]

17:06.958 --> 17:08.750
- [exhales sharply]
- [beeps]

17:08.750 --> 17:11.625
[Bud] <i>All of our work,
everything that we've accomplished</i>

17:11.625 --> 17:14.916
<i>is the result
of this fruit-bearing collaboration</i>

17:14.916 --> 17:18.750
<i>between like-minded corporations
that make America great.</i>

17:20.916 --> 17:23.750
On behalf of everyone here at Vault-Tec...

17:25.000 --> 17:26.625
...welcome.

17:31.833 --> 17:34.416
Let's call this what it is, Bud.

17:34.416 --> 17:36.583
Your sales aren't up to snuff,

17:36.583 --> 17:38.208
and you need money.

17:38.208 --> 17:41.833
You're one to talk, Freddy boy.
You could lose money running a casino.

17:41.833 --> 17:43.916
[laughing]

17:45.416 --> 17:47.291
[Bud] <i>Our sales are fine.</i>

17:47.291 --> 17:50.125
<i>Sure, rumors of the peace
negotiations have set us back a bit,</i>

17:50.125 --> 17:53.125
<i>but we're here
to offer you an opportunity.</i>

17:53.125 --> 17:55.500
<i>We'd like to collaborate
on some of our vaults.</i>

17:55.500 --> 17:57.666
[Leon] <i>I-I don't get the vaults.</i>

17:57.666 --> 17:59.125
<i>When it's time to come out,</i>

17:59.125 --> 18:02.708
what if people are still alive
on the surface?

18:02.708 --> 18:04.500
They'll be Stone Age creatures.

18:04.500 --> 18:07.250
Probably eat whoever
steps out of your vaults.

18:07.250 --> 18:08.583
That isn't an issue.

18:08.583 --> 18:11.791
Our vaults have the resources
to survive for centuries.

18:11.791 --> 18:14.583
Meanwhile, our competitors-- you know,

18:14.583 --> 18:18.458
every other human who isn't us--
will be dead on the surface.

18:19.750 --> 18:21.291
<i>Because after all,</i>

18:21.291 --> 18:24.791
what is the ultimate weapon
of mass destruction?

18:29.000 --> 18:30.125
Time.

18:30.125 --> 18:31.625
<i>Time.</i>

18:32.708 --> 18:35.458
Time is the apex predator.

18:35.458 --> 18:37.791
And in the event of an incident,

18:37.791 --> 18:42.500
time is the weapon with which
we will defeat all of our enemies.

18:42.500 --> 18:46.041
<i>That is how we will win
the great game of capitalism.</i>

18:46.041 --> 18:48.666
<i>Not by outfighting anyone,</i>

18:48.666 --> 18:50.166
but by outliving them.

18:50.166 --> 18:51.875
[Robert] Even if you outlive

18:51.875 --> 18:56.083
all external threats,
here's my problem with the vaults.

18:56.083 --> 18:58.291
You confine a bunch of rats

18:58.291 --> 19:01.166
in a nest for a long time,
they end up eating each other.

19:01.166 --> 19:03.208
So who's to say your rats
are gonna survive

19:03.208 --> 19:06.041
better than those animals on the surface?

19:06.041 --> 19:08.208
And you still haven't addressed
the fundamental question--

19:08.208 --> 19:09.416
That is a little shortsighted,
I would say.

19:09.416 --> 19:10.791
I don't need rats
for people on the surface.

19:10.791 --> 19:13.375
[overlapping chatter]

19:13.375 --> 19:15.625
- [chuckles]
- [overlapping chatter]

19:15.625 --> 19:17.708
- [overlapping chatter continues]
- [suspenseful music playing]

19:22.250 --> 19:24.250
- [beeps]
- [overlapping chatter continues]

19:30.458 --> 19:34.333
If I could perhaps
refocus the conversation.

19:34.333 --> 19:35.541
[chatter stops]

19:38.833 --> 19:41.750
Come on, Barb. Set 'em straight.

19:42.916 --> 19:46.083
When I think about the future,

19:46.083 --> 19:49.291
I think about my daughter...

19:49.291 --> 19:51.041
Janey.

19:51.041 --> 19:53.166
[sighs]

19:53.166 --> 19:54.750
<i>How do I provide her</i>

19:54.750 --> 19:56.916
with a better future?

19:56.916 --> 20:00.541
That's what we've invited you here
to discuss.

20:00.541 --> 20:02.333
Yes. [sighs]

20:02.333 --> 20:04.875
<i>And how do we design</i>

20:04.875 --> 20:10.250
our vault societies
so our children have that better future?

20:10.250 --> 20:12.750
I suggest we hedge our bets.

20:12.750 --> 20:15.541
[Brain-on-a-Roomba] <i>Wait!
I am the Overseer here!</i>

20:15.541 --> 20:17.916
<i>My orders must be followed!</i>

20:17.916 --> 20:21.416
<i>Why isn't this working?
This is conflict resolution 101.</i>

20:21.416 --> 20:23.166
[Norm] Where's the rest of the vault?

20:23.166 --> 20:25.333
<i>This is the rest of the vault.</i>

20:25.333 --> 20:28.250
Is this where my dad's from?

20:28.250 --> 20:30.416
<i>You'll never find out.</i>

20:31.458 --> 20:33.333
- [lights clack on]
<i>- Oh. He's gonna find out.</i>

20:33.333 --> 20:36.583
[machines powering up]

20:42.625 --> 20:44.958
[suspenseful music playing]

20:51.958 --> 20:54.166
[Brain-on-a-Roomba] <i>These are Bud's Buds.</i>

20:54.166 --> 20:58.625
<i>My Buds. America outsourced the survival
of this country to the private sector.</i>

20:58.625 --> 21:01.291
<i>But it would have been insane
to keep a failed nation alive.</i>

21:01.291 --> 21:04.583
<i>So, we kept Vault-Tec alive instead.</i>

21:04.583 --> 21:08.083
<i>A well-trained staff
of highly supervised junior executives</i>

21:08.083 --> 21:09.500
<i>from my own assistant training program.</i>

21:11.083 --> 21:15.000
<i>Because the future of humanity
comes down to one word:</i>

21:15.000 --> 21:17.291
<i>Management.</i>

21:18.833 --> 21:21.250
[Barb] Bud here has an idea for

21:21.250 --> 21:23.541
three interconnected vaults.

21:23.541 --> 21:27.291
But we need more ideas.
We need your ideas.

21:27.291 --> 21:31.500
Because it was the spirit of competition
that made our companies great,

21:31.500 --> 21:37.583
and I propose we bring that same spirit
of competition to our solution.

21:37.583 --> 21:41.000
[map dinging]

21:41.000 --> 21:45.833
We have over a hundred vaults
spread across America.

21:46.833 --> 21:50.291
Enough for each of you to claim several,

21:50.291 --> 21:53.416
where you can play out your own ideas

21:53.416 --> 21:57.208
for how to create the perfect conditions
for humanity.

21:57.208 --> 22:00.541
Whatever you want to do,
no one needs to know.

22:03.291 --> 22:05.083
And may the best idea win.

22:06.333 --> 22:08.500
[whirring]

22:09.833 --> 22:14.250
So what's Vault 32 and 33?
Just people to be controlled?

22:14.250 --> 22:18.125
<i>What? No! When you put it like that,
it sounds downright morally questionable.</i>

22:18.125 --> 22:23.041
<i>They're our breeding pool,
the ultimate expression of HR R&D.</i>

22:23.041 --> 22:27.125
<i>Genetically selected to breed with my Buds
to create a class of super managers.</i>

22:27.125 --> 22:30.666
<i>People with positivity,
people who make lemonade.</i>

22:30.666 --> 22:34.333
<i>People who will inherit the Earth
after we've wiped the surface clean.</i>

22:38.083 --> 22:40.625
We wiped the surface clean?

22:40.625 --> 22:42.666
[Frederick] <i>We could intentionally</i>

22:42.666 --> 22:49.000
overcrowd a vault so people have
to compete to survive inside it.

22:49.000 --> 22:53.166
We have been developing a robot
that delivers milk to the front door.

22:53.166 --> 22:56.166
It's quite intelligent. I would like
to see a vault governed by it.

22:56.166 --> 23:00.083
What about using a vault
to develop a super-mutant soldier

23:00.083 --> 23:01.875
using illegal immigrants?

23:01.875 --> 23:04.666
[man] <i>We could pump
psychotropic drugs into the air supply.</i>

23:04.666 --> 23:06.958
[woman] <i>We could separate
parents and children,</i>

23:06.958 --> 23:09.166
<i>and only the smartest kids
reach adulthood.</i>

23:09.166 --> 23:11.083
[Robert] <i>It's a fun idea.</i>

23:11.083 --> 23:15.208
There's a lot of earning potential
with the end of the world.

23:15.208 --> 23:18.875
But we're talking
about making a significant investment

23:18.875 --> 23:21.000
based on a hypothetical.

23:21.000 --> 23:23.333
How can you guarantee results?

23:24.333 --> 23:26.583
By dropping the bomb ourselves.

23:27.875 --> 23:30.375
[staticky ringing]

23:30.375 --> 23:31.875
[indistinct chatter over earbud]

23:31.875 --> 23:33.375
[Betty] Mr. Howard?

23:33.375 --> 23:35.500
[chatter continues over earbud]

23:35.500 --> 23:37.125
Mr. Howard?

23:39.208 --> 23:41.916
Everything all right, Mr. Howard?

23:41.916 --> 23:45.541
Uh, fine.
I'm-I'm... I'm-I'm fine, Betty.

23:46.875 --> 23:48.916
He is so excited to meet you.

23:52.208 --> 23:55.583
A nuclear event would be a tragedy...

23:55.583 --> 23:58.416
but also, an opportunity.

23:58.416 --> 24:01.541
Perhaps the greatest opportunity
in history.

24:01.541 --> 24:06.250
Because when we are the only ones left,
there will be no one to fight.

24:08.291 --> 24:10.666
A true monopoly.

24:10.666 --> 24:12.500
- [door closes]
- Mr. Howard.

24:12.500 --> 24:15.125
Huge fan. I'm Henry, but, uh,

24:15.125 --> 24:17.208
everyone calls me Hank.

24:18.666 --> 24:20.291
Wow.

24:20.291 --> 24:22.958
[eerie, ominous music playing]

24:24.333 --> 24:28.208
[Moldaver] <i>Your father has been around
for a very long time.</i>

24:28.208 --> 24:31.291
- [speaking indistinctly]
- [high-pitched ringing]

24:33.333 --> 24:35.333
[Moldaver] <i>Part of an organization</i>

24:35.333 --> 24:38.583
<i>that thought they had the answers
to all the world's problems.</i>

24:42.041 --> 24:44.166
[Young Hank] <i>You know, that scene?</i>

24:44.166 --> 24:46.500
That scene where
you shoot Joey Toro in the face?

24:48.291 --> 24:51.708
<i>Feo, fuerte y formal.</i>

24:51.708 --> 24:57.000
[Barb] <i>This is our chance
to make war obsolete.</i>

24:57.000 --> 25:02.208
<i>Because in our current societal
configuration, which took shape without</i>

25:02.208 --> 25:05.583
intentional guidance, we have friction.

25:06.958 --> 25:09.625
We have conflict, and we have war.

25:12.000 --> 25:14.083
And war, well...

25:19.916 --> 25:22.125
War never changes.

25:23.708 --> 25:27.000
- [indistinct chatter]
- [high-pitched ringing]

25:27.000 --> 25:29.833
[Young Hank] I was just wondering,
if-if... if you don't mind,

25:29.833 --> 25:33.958
um, I hate to be that guy, but, do you
think you could give me an autograph?

25:36.958 --> 25:39.541
[Moldaver] He never told you
where he's really from,

25:39.541 --> 25:41.750
when he's from.

25:42.750 --> 25:45.750
He never told your mother, either.

25:55.833 --> 25:57.666
What do you know about my mother?

25:58.916 --> 26:01.416
She was like you.

26:01.416 --> 26:04.875
She was kind, loving.

26:04.875 --> 26:06.375
Curious.

26:06.375 --> 26:09.083
Isn't that why you came
to the surface really?

26:09.083 --> 26:12.041
Partly to rescue your father, but...

26:12.041 --> 26:14.541
to know why I took him?

26:14.541 --> 26:16.666
[machines clicking, whirring]

26:21.416 --> 26:23.416
[indistinct chatter]

26:30.583 --> 26:33.333
[slow, suspenseful music playing]

26:33.333 --> 26:35.833
[weapons clicking]

26:35.833 --> 26:38.000
Thank you.

26:45.250 --> 26:47.708
Wait. Dane, they're sending you?

26:47.708 --> 26:50.083
Punishment for what I did to myself.

26:51.166 --> 26:52.166
Hey.

26:54.375 --> 26:55.958
I was just scared of going into the Wilds.

26:55.958 --> 26:59.041
I had no idea
they'd blame you for it. I...

27:00.333 --> 27:01.750
I'm sorry.

27:01.750 --> 27:04.750
[slow, dramatic music playing]

27:04.750 --> 27:06.541
Don't be.

27:06.541 --> 27:09.208
I was meant to go on that mission.

27:11.458 --> 27:13.250
I met someone.

27:13.250 --> 27:16.291
But right now, she's walking into danger.

27:16.291 --> 27:18.500
That's why you came back.

27:18.500 --> 27:20.583
To rescue her.

27:21.750 --> 27:23.375
[whispering] I'm leaving with her.

27:23.375 --> 27:25.500
I am going back to where she came from.

27:25.500 --> 27:30.833
A vault. It's a place
that's peaceful... and safe.

27:30.833 --> 27:32.666
Where nobody ever goes to war.

27:34.458 --> 27:36.666
What?

27:36.666 --> 27:39.000
- Maggots, clear out!
- [others] Yes, sir!

27:39.000 --> 27:40.875
[overlapping shouting]

27:40.875 --> 27:42.750
[engines whirring]

27:44.250 --> 27:46.500
There's nowhere safe, Max.

27:46.500 --> 27:48.875
And there's no leaving.

27:48.875 --> 27:50.541
I wish there was.

27:57.291 --> 27:59.291
♪ ♪

28:09.791 --> 28:13.083
[dramatic music playing]

28:33.000 --> 28:35.291
[Moldaver] Rose was so clever.

28:35.291 --> 28:37.416
Like you.

28:38.791 --> 28:42.458
Lucy, your mother discovered

28:42.458 --> 28:45.541
that something was siphoning
the vault's water away.

28:45.541 --> 28:48.083
[somber music playing]

28:48.083 --> 28:50.125
From that one clue,

28:50.125 --> 28:52.958
she deduced that maybe...

28:52.958 --> 28:55.583
civilization had returned to the surface.

29:02.208 --> 29:04.583
When she told her husband,

29:04.583 --> 29:07.791
he said it was a ridiculous idea,

29:07.791 --> 29:10.041
and that she should tell no one.

29:10.041 --> 29:12.833
Lucy, let's go. Let's--

29:12.833 --> 29:17.875
And that's when she realized
that her husband, the Overseer,

29:17.875 --> 29:19.416
was hiding things.

29:19.416 --> 29:21.625
[Hank] Lucy, let's go.
Let's get out of here.

29:21.625 --> 29:23.958
[Moldaver] So she ran away.

29:23.958 --> 29:25.958
Like you did, Lucy.

29:28.166 --> 29:30.958
<i>And took her children.</i>

29:30.958 --> 29:33.750
And she found this wonderful city

29:33.750 --> 29:36.500
that was everything
the vaults had promised to be.

29:36.500 --> 29:38.958
[Hank] <i>She is lying!</i>

29:38.958 --> 29:40.083
[Moldaver] <i>But then,</i>

29:40.083 --> 29:42.625
her husband came after her.

29:42.625 --> 29:46.375
And when she decided not to return home,

29:46.375 --> 29:48.208
he took the children.

29:51.250 --> 29:54.500
And he burned that city to the ground.

29:59.500 --> 30:01.166
Shady Sands.

30:01.166 --> 30:02.666
She's lying, Lucy.

30:04.250 --> 30:06.875
[Moldaver] <i>That's how
Vault-Tec deals with competition.</i>

30:06.875 --> 30:10.000
<i>Just like they did 200 years ago.</i>

30:14.833 --> 30:16.833
[gentle music playing]

30:30.833 --> 30:33.083
[bell clanging]

30:34.166 --> 30:36.000
Lucy?

30:36.000 --> 30:39.000
What you brought me is cold fusion.

30:39.000 --> 30:40.625
It's limitless energy.

30:40.625 --> 30:42.250
- Lucy?
- And we can build--

30:42.250 --> 30:44.000
- She's a murderer.
- ...our own world.

30:44.000 --> 30:46.083
- Lucy, look at me.
- It could be a better world.

30:46.083 --> 30:48.125
- It has clean water and medicine--
- [Hank] She invaded our home.

30:48.125 --> 30:49.458
[Moldaver] <i>...and power.</i>

30:49.458 --> 30:50.875
- <i>But for everyone.</i>
- [Hank] <i>Lucy?</i>

30:50.875 --> 30:52.375
- Because when Vault-Tec...
- She killed...

30:52.375 --> 30:54.083
- ...bought my research...
- ...our people...

30:54.083 --> 30:56.250
[Moldaver] ...they made it proprietary,

30:56.250 --> 30:59.000
so only a trusted Vault-Tec minion

30:59.000 --> 31:03.833
- can activate cold fusion.
- Do not listen to her.

31:04.875 --> 31:06.833
[Moldaver] All I need

31:06.833 --> 31:08.916
is for him to give me the code.

31:08.916 --> 31:12.000
- Lucy, look at me!
- [banging stool on bars]

31:12.000 --> 31:13.416
Look at me!

31:13.416 --> 31:14.875
Lucy!

31:14.875 --> 31:16.958
[panting]

31:18.708 --> 31:20.916
[somber music playing]

31:27.125 --> 31:28.583
My mother.

31:31.916 --> 31:33.958
What happened to her?

31:36.833 --> 31:39.250
- I think you know.
- [Hank scoffs]

31:46.208 --> 31:48.666
[ghoul gasping]

31:58.458 --> 31:59.541
[Rose] <i>Lucy?</i>

31:59.541 --> 32:01.958
- [speaking indistinctly]
- [gentle music playing]

32:21.458 --> 32:23.791
[sniffles]

32:23.791 --> 32:25.458
[gasps]

32:25.458 --> 32:28.625
- [Hank] Lucy?
- [gasps]

32:28.625 --> 32:30.708
She's lying, Lucy.

32:35.250 --> 32:37.416
Just give her the code.

32:44.833 --> 32:46.833
[gasps softly]

32:53.208 --> 32:55.250
Give her the code.

33:06.208 --> 33:08.208
Give her the code, Dad.

33:09.750 --> 33:11.750
[sighs]

33:12.916 --> 33:14.916
[sniffles]

33:19.666 --> 33:23.041
[sighs, sniffles]

33:32.833 --> 33:34.541
[Lucy gasps softly]

33:38.458 --> 33:39.500
[beeping]

33:42.958 --> 33:44.125
[chimes]

33:44.125 --> 33:46.208
[beeping continues]

33:47.541 --> 33:49.916
[rotational trilling]

33:51.458 --> 33:53.166
[whirring]

33:56.291 --> 33:59.291
[triumphant music playing]

33:59.291 --> 34:02.291
[high-pitched whirring]

34:07.791 --> 34:10.041
♪ ♪

34:24.125 --> 34:26.125
♪ ♪

34:38.541 --> 34:41.541
[slow, suspenseful music playing]

34:45.458 --> 34:48.083
[whirring]

34:48.083 --> 34:50.166
[soft beeping]

34:58.500 --> 34:59.625
[whirring]

35:04.416 --> 35:06.875
Well, it was great meeting you.
I actually have to get back home.

35:06.875 --> 35:09.750
[Brain-on-a-Roomba] <i>You can't go home,
son of Hank.</i>

35:11.041 --> 35:12.916
No.

35:15.000 --> 35:16.875
<i>Not with what you've learned.</i>

35:19.416 --> 35:22.541
So you're just--
you're just gonna keep me here?

35:22.541 --> 35:24.916
<i>Just until we're all ready
to go to the surface.</i>

35:24.916 --> 35:26.458
That could be hundreds of years.

35:26.458 --> 35:30.125
<i>True. That's why I'd suggest
you wait it out in your dad's pod.</i>

35:30.125 --> 35:32.333
<i>Unless you want to starve to death.</i>

35:32.333 --> 35:36.125
<i>Not much food in here,
except the occasional very large bug.</i>

35:36.125 --> 35:39.291
<i>I'd certainly put myself
to sleep if I could.</i>

35:43.125 --> 35:45.583
[breathing heavily]

35:53.291 --> 35:56.291
[eerie, suspenseful music playing]

36:12.166 --> 36:15.333
[somber music playing]

36:15.333 --> 36:18.291
I did what was necessary...

36:20.208 --> 36:22.208
...to save our people.

36:24.083 --> 36:25.666
And that woman over there...

36:25.666 --> 36:28.083
[keypad clicking, beeping]

36:28.083 --> 36:30.375
She's no different than me.

36:39.458 --> 36:42.041
[beeps, trills]

36:43.250 --> 36:45.500
[whooshing]

36:46.833 --> 36:48.833
[high-pitched whirring]

36:56.041 --> 36:59.083
- [air raid sirens blaring]
- [Lucy gasps]

36:59.083 --> 37:01.666
[soldier] <i>Incoming aircraft.</i>

37:01.666 --> 37:03.166
[air raid sirens continue]

37:03.166 --> 37:04.833
The Brotherhood?

37:04.833 --> 37:06.791
Barricade the doors!

37:07.875 --> 37:10.000
Don't let anyone in here!

37:10.000 --> 37:11.333
Let's move!

37:11.333 --> 37:14.250
- [indistinct shouting]
- [soldier] Move out, move out, move out.

37:14.250 --> 37:16.958
[shouting fades in distance]

37:16.958 --> 37:18.666
[Hank] Lucy?

37:18.666 --> 37:20.833
I loved your mother.

37:23.041 --> 37:26.041
But she stopped being your mother
when she left home.

37:27.875 --> 37:31.750
When she took you into danger.

37:35.375 --> 37:38.916
[dramatic, majestic music playing]

37:43.333 --> 37:45.583
[indistinct radio chatter]

37:45.583 --> 37:48.625
[retching]

37:48.625 --> 37:50.708
[Vertibird blades whirring]

37:56.625 --> 37:58.625
[mechanical whirring]

38:06.416 --> 38:08.666
- [alarm blaring]
- Incoming!

38:11.541 --> 38:13.166
[screams]

38:13.166 --> 38:14.791
You've seen what it's like up here.

38:25.375 --> 38:29.333
<i>Everyone equally afraid,
equally miserable.</i>

38:37.125 --> 38:40.333
<i>Forced to do horrible things
in order to survive.</i>

38:41.375 --> 38:43.541
Lucy...

38:43.541 --> 38:47.125
I had to make a choice.

38:49.541 --> 38:54.208
<i>Between their violent world
and our peaceful one.</i>

38:54.208 --> 38:57.041
[somber music playing]

38:57.041 --> 39:02.083
And I believe, Lucy, I know
I made the right choice.

39:29.125 --> 39:32.375
[high-pitched ringing]

39:32.375 --> 39:35.041
- [♪ Nat King Cole:
"I Don't Want to See Tomorrow"]
- <i>♪ I don't want to see ♪</i>

39:35.041 --> 39:39.458
<i>♪ Tomorrow ♪</i>

39:39.458 --> 39:41.833
<i>♪ Unless ♪</i>

39:41.833 --> 39:44.125
<i>♪ I see it ♪</i>

39:44.125 --> 39:47.500
<i>♪ With you ♪</i>

39:48.583 --> 39:52.250
<i>♪ Tomorrow, so they say ♪</i>

39:52.250 --> 39:55.708
<i>♪ Will be a lovely day ♪</i>

39:55.708 --> 39:59.000
<i>♪ A bright new sun will suddenly ♪</i>

39:59.000 --> 40:00.958
<i>♪ Break through ♪</i>

40:02.000 --> 40:04.666
<i>♪ But I don't want to see ♪</i>

40:04.666 --> 40:06.041
Go!

40:06.041 --> 40:08.375
<i>♪ Tomorrow ♪</i>

40:08.375 --> 40:13.833
<i>♪ Unless I see it with you ♪</i>

40:14.875 --> 40:16.416
<i>♪ Tomorrow, so I hear...</i>

40:16.416 --> 40:20.250
[Hank] If the problem with the world
is factions endlessly fighting,

40:20.250 --> 40:23.208
endlessly at war,
then what is the solution

40:23.208 --> 40:25.291
but to get rid of the factions?

40:25.291 --> 40:28.458
To make the world us,

40:28.458 --> 40:30.166
only ours to shape.

40:30.166 --> 40:34.416
<i>♪ To see tomorrow ♪</i>

40:34.416 --> 40:38.875
<i>♪ Unless you're there by my side ♪</i>

40:41.791 --> 40:44.833
<i>♪ Don't want to walk alone ♪</i>

40:44.833 --> 40:48.083
<i>♪ Don't want to dream alone ♪</i>

40:48.083 --> 40:53.333
<i>♪ Just want you close to my heart ♪</i>

40:53.333 --> 40:54.625
[explosion]

40:54.625 --> 40:57.458
<i>♪ For if your love is gone ♪</i>

40:57.458 --> 41:00.791
<i>♪ How can I face the dawn of Sunday ♪</i>

41:00.791 --> 41:03.125
<i>♪ Or Monday? ♪</i>

41:03.125 --> 41:05.750
<i>♪ I just can't face one day ♪</i>

41:05.750 --> 41:09.916
<i>♪ Until you say you're mine ♪</i>

41:09.916 --> 41:13.291
<i>♪ Oh, darling, please be mine ♪</i>

41:13.291 --> 41:18.125
<i>♪ And make each bright tomorrow
young and new ♪</i>

41:19.250 --> 41:25.125
<i>♪ But I don't want to face tomorrow ♪</i>

41:25.125 --> 41:27.666
<i>♪ Unless ♪</i>

41:27.666 --> 41:29.625
<i>♪ I see it ♪</i>

41:29.625 --> 41:31.333
[whistles]

41:31.333 --> 41:34.666
<i>♪ With you ♪</i>

41:39.208 --> 41:40.916
[ominous music playing]

41:40.916 --> 41:44.125
I'll bet that outfit makes y'all feel
like a big man, don't it?

41:45.250 --> 41:49.291
Well, I know 'cause,
well, I used to wear one

41:49.291 --> 41:51.041
back in the day.

41:51.041 --> 41:53.625
There was only one problem with it.

41:53.625 --> 41:55.916
There was a flaw

41:55.916 --> 41:59.875
in the welding just below the chest plate.

42:01.291 --> 42:03.791
I wonder if they fixed that
in this new model?

42:13.000 --> 42:15.833
I guess not.

42:15.833 --> 42:18.791
[exciting music playing]

42:27.583 --> 42:28.625
[soldier] Did you get him?

42:28.625 --> 42:30.166
[Knight] I can't see shit.

42:39.708 --> 42:41.208
Find that fucking ghoul.

42:55.708 --> 42:59.875
Open the door, Lucy.
Open the door, let's go home.

42:59.875 --> 43:01.750
[tense music playing]

43:01.750 --> 43:03.416
Let's go home.

43:09.625 --> 43:10.875
Let's go home.

43:14.125 --> 43:16.125
[ghoul breathing heavily]

43:24.958 --> 43:26.750
[Hank] Lucy.

43:33.000 --> 43:35.958
Please. Open the door, Lucy.

43:38.250 --> 43:40.333
[distant explosion]

43:45.916 --> 43:47.958
[dramatic music playing]

43:56.625 --> 43:59.958
[Maximus] Lucy. Lucy.

43:59.958 --> 44:01.333
Lucy?

44:01.333 --> 44:03.583
- Lucy.
- [Hank] Hey. Hey.

44:03.583 --> 44:05.750
I'm her father.
Can you get us out of here?

44:08.666 --> 44:11.750
- Lucy, let's go. Come on,
we got to get out of here.
- Wait. No.

44:11.750 --> 44:13.666
Not with him.

44:13.666 --> 44:15.250
Why not with him? What do you mean?

44:15.250 --> 44:17.708
Because it was him. He...

44:17.708 --> 44:19.625
- What?
- It was him.

44:19.625 --> 44:21.625
- What was him?
- He...

44:22.916 --> 44:25.291
Lucy, what?

44:27.291 --> 44:29.291
Shady Sands.

44:32.208 --> 44:33.958
[dramatic music playing]

44:55.833 --> 44:58.000
It was him.

45:02.625 --> 45:04.333
I'm sorry.

45:04.333 --> 45:07.416
[tense, dramatic music playing]

45:10.791 --> 45:14.125
Lucy. You're coming with me.

45:14.125 --> 45:16.083
[yells]

45:17.250 --> 45:18.833
No!

45:20.750 --> 45:24.708
Hey, Max. Max. Max, wake up.

45:28.708 --> 45:31.166
[suspenseful music playing]

45:36.833 --> 45:39.625
You see what this place does to people?

45:41.166 --> 45:43.166
I'm your father, Lucy.

45:46.958 --> 45:49.708
You came all this way for me.

45:55.666 --> 45:57.750
You're not gonna hurt me.

46:08.958 --> 46:12.083
[grunts] God...

46:12.083 --> 46:15.083
Oh, you want another autograph,
Young Henry?

46:16.375 --> 46:20.708
<i>Feo, fuerte y formal.</i>

46:23.083 --> 46:26.708
When your daughter said her last name
was MacLean, well,

46:26.708 --> 46:30.708
I just couldn't believe
it was the MacLean.

46:30.708 --> 46:34.083
Hell, this kid used to pick up
my wife's dry cleaning.

46:35.291 --> 46:38.250
Now, I've waited over 200 years

46:38.250 --> 46:42.500
to ask somebody one question.

46:43.833 --> 46:46.041
Where's my fucking family?

46:46.041 --> 46:48.458
[tense, dramatic music playing]

47:05.875 --> 47:07.333
Yeah.

47:09.125 --> 47:11.333
[grunts]

47:11.333 --> 47:12.791
[Lucy] Hey.

47:12.791 --> 47:17.583
Max. Hey, hey. Hey, Max. Max, wake up.

47:17.583 --> 47:19.291
Come on, wake up.

47:19.291 --> 47:22.708
Wake up! God. [grunts]

47:22.708 --> 47:25.625
Come on. Come on!

47:25.625 --> 47:29.000
Come on! Please!

47:31.416 --> 47:32.750
[grunts]

47:34.500 --> 47:36.500
♪ ♪

47:39.458 --> 47:41.708
[gunfire continues in distance]

47:44.375 --> 47:47.875
War never changes.

47:47.875 --> 47:51.125
You look out at this Wasteland,

47:51.125 --> 47:53.333
looks like chaos.

47:57.541 --> 47:59.958
But there's always somebody
behind the wheel.

48:01.791 --> 48:04.208
And that's who I want to talk to.

48:06.583 --> 48:08.333
That's where your daddy is headed.

48:08.333 --> 48:10.333
But you let him go.

48:10.333 --> 48:15.208
[Ghoul] Well, it's easier to track a stuck
pig than to ask it where it's off to.

48:18.750 --> 48:20.833
You want to know
how I know your daddy, don't you?

48:20.833 --> 48:25.541
Let's just say that everything
about your whole little world

48:25.541 --> 48:27.708
was decided over 200 years ago.

48:31.958 --> 48:34.583
Now, you can stay here with him,

48:34.583 --> 48:37.125
but when his tin can soldier friends
take this place--

48:37.125 --> 48:39.916
and they gonna take this place--

48:39.916 --> 48:42.875
they will kill you and everybody here.

48:42.875 --> 48:46.750
[somber music playing]

48:53.250 --> 48:56.083
Or you could come meet your makers.

49:00.625 --> 49:02.625
[dramatic music playing]

49:06.000 --> 49:08.791
♪ ♪

49:13.291 --> 49:15.333
[gun cocks]

49:30.416 --> 49:32.958
[gurgles]

49:42.083 --> 49:44.291
[sighs]

49:45.416 --> 49:46.875
You coming?

49:54.666 --> 49:57.166
[somber music playing]

49:57.166 --> 49:58.583
Hey.

50:01.250 --> 50:02.416
Get up.

50:07.375 --> 50:09.125
Max.

50:12.000 --> 50:13.541
I'll find you.

50:35.833 --> 50:37.416
Okey-dokey.

50:57.000 --> 51:00.000
